# Analysis of the Main Target Image

The target image shows two separate structures standing on a dark checkered floor:

## Structure 1 (Left Structure):
- This is a vertical rectangular structure with yellow sides and green blocks at the top and bottom
- It has an opening in the middle showing a blue cube on top of a red cube
- Total Layers: 3 (bottom green layer, middle yellow layer with opening, top green layer)
- Total Blocks: 5 (2 green rectangular blocks, 1 yellow frame block, 1 blue cube, 1 red cube)

## Structure 2 (Right Structure):
- This is a more complex structure with red blocks with circular/arch openings
- It has yellow horizontal rectangular blocks on top and in the middle
- Total Layers: 3 (bottom red arch block, middle section with red block with circular hole and yellow block, top yellow block)
- Total Blocks: 4 (3 red blocks - one with double arches at bottom, one with circular hole in middle, and one additional piece; 2 yellow horizontal blocks)

# Required Blocks from Dictionary

## Structure 1 (Left Structure):
- Green horizontal rectangular blocks (indices 10 and 11) for top and bottom
- Yellow vertical rectangular block (index 15) for the frame
- Blue cube (index 7) for upper interior cube
- Red cube (index 9) for lower interior cube

## Structure 2 (Right Structure):
- Red block with double arches (index 1) for the bottom
- Red block with circular hole (index 6) for the middle
- Yellow horizontal rectangular blocks (indices 14 and 16) for the top and middle

# Assembly Order

```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1
    Step2: Move block with index 16
    Step3: Move block with index 6
    Step4: Move block with index 14
    Step5: Move block with index 11
    Step6: Move block with index 15
    Step7: Move block with index 7
    Step8: Move block with index 9
    Step9: Move block with index 10
}
```

This assembly sequence builds the right structure first (steps 1-4), then constructs the left structure (steps 5-9), working from bottom to top for both structures.
